# GraphRAG Pipeline

## Pipeline Stages (in order)

```
Upload PDF
  → text chunk (DOCUMENT_CHUNK_SIZE / DOCUMENT_CHUNK_OVERLAP)
  → entity extraction   (parallel, batched, LLM)
  → relationship extraction (parallel, per-chunk, LLM)
  → save graph to Neo4j  → triggers background pipeline ↓

Background pipeline (tracked in Redis by pipeline_job_id):
  1. community_detection   Hierarchical Louvain: Leaf → Mid → Root
  2. summarizing           LLM community reports per node/level
  3. embedding             text-embedding-3-small on entities + summaries
  → Brain persisted to Neo4j, cache warmed in Redis
```

## Key Services

| Service | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `entity_extraction_service` | Chunk → entity + description ("Identity Card") |
| `relationship_extraction_service` | Chunk + entity list → edges |
| `community_detection_service` | Louvain 3-level hierarchy |
| `summarization_service` | LLM reports per community (leaf/mid/root) |
| `embedding_service` | OpenAI embeddings → Neo4j vector indexes |
| `neo4j_service` | All Neo4j I/O, vector indexes, brain node |
| `brain_pipeline_service` | Orchestrates steps 1-3; single canonical path used everywhere |

## Data Scoping Rules
- All Neo4j nodes carry `user_id` (PostgreSQL UUID string) **and** `document_name`
- Community nodes use `derived_user_id` (not `user_id`) to avoid collisions with source graph queries
- Entity embeddings are keyed `(user_id, document_name, id)` — same entity id in two documents is intentionally isolated

## Fingerprint-Aware Embedding
Entity Identity Cards and community summaries store a **content hash** alongside their embedding. Re-running the pipeline skips re-embedding nodes whose hash hasn't changed, saving OpenAI calls.

## LLM Retry Policy
Configured via env vars: `LLM_RETRY_MAX_ATTEMPTS`, `LLM_RETRY_BASE_DELAY_MS`, `LLM_RETRY_MAX_DELAY_MS`

## Prompts
JSON files in `backend/app/prompts/`. Loaded and cached by `PromptManager`.
- `entity_extraction.json` — extract entities with description field
- `relationship_extraction.json` — edges between known entities only
- `community_summary.json` — per-community LLM report (leaf/mid/root)

Edit the JSON to change prompt wording. Call `PromptManager.reload_prompt(name)` to hot-reload without restart.

## Adding a New Pipeline Step
1. Create a service in `backend/app/services/`
2. Register the step inside `brain_pipeline_service` (single canonical path)
3. Add a Redis progress key so the frontend stepper can track it
4. Expose a `step` string in `GET /graph/pipeline/status/{id}` response
5. Update the frontend `ProcessingSteps.tsx` stepper labels

## Neo4j Vector Indexes
- `entity_embedding_idx` — entity Identity Card embeddings (local / specific-fact search)
- `community_summary_embedding_idx` — community summary embeddings (global / theme search)
- Index dimensions are derived at runtime from `EMBEDDING_MODEL` — do not hardcode

## Brain Refresh vs Re-run
- `GET /community/brain` → **read-only** — fetches persisted brain, never re-runs pipeline
- `POST /community/detect` → **full re-run** — manual / programmatic only
- The dashboard Refresh button always uses the read-only endpoint
